01:42:57.340 --> 01:43:01.660
but Turing never intended it to be a computer architecture.

01:43:01.660 --> 01:43:06.340
He used it just to prove results about uncomputability.

01:43:07.420 --> 01:43:10.900
What Turing did on what his computation is exquisite

01:43:10.900 --> 01:43:12.700
is gorgeous.

01:43:12.700 --> 01:43:16.420
He gave us our notion of computational universality

01:43:16.420 --> 01:43:19.740
and something that sounds deep

01:43:19.740 --> 01:43:24.740
and turns out to be trivial is it's really easy

01:43:25.060 --> 01:43:29.300
to show almost everything is computationally universal.

01:43:29.300 --> 01:43:33.340
So Norm Margolis wrote a beautiful paper

01:43:34.820 --> 01:43:39.180
with Tom Toffoli showing in a cellular automata world

01:43:39.180 --> 01:43:41.660
is like the game of life

01:43:41.660 --> 01:43:43.940
where you just move tokens around.

01:43:45.580 --> 01:43:48.660
They showed that modeling billiard balls

01:43:48.660 --> 01:43:52.420
on a billiard table with cellular automata

01:43:52.420 --> 01:43:53.900
is a universal computer.

01:43:54.900 --> 01:43:59.620
To be universal, you need a persistent state.

01:43:59.620 --> 01:44:03.020
You need a non-linear operation to interact them

01:44:04.700 --> 01:44:08.380
and you need connectivity.

01:44:08.380 --> 01:44:11.420
So that's what you need to show computational universality.

01:44:11.420 --> 01:44:15.660
So they showed that a CA modeling billiard balls

01:44:15.660 --> 01:44:17.620
is a universal computer.

01:44:17.620 --> 01:44:21.780
Chris Moore went on to show that instead of chaos,

01:44:22.780 --> 01:44:27.140
Turing showed their problems in computation

01:44:27.140 --> 01:44:30.340
that you can't solve, that they're harder

01:44:30.340 --> 01:44:31.340
than you can't predict.

01:44:31.340 --> 01:44:34.700
They're actually in a deep reason that they are unsolvable.

01:44:36.140 --> 01:44:39.300
Chris Moore showed it's very easy to make physical systems

01:44:39.300 --> 01:44:43.380
that are uncomputable, that what the physics system does,

01:44:43.380 --> 01:44:45.500
just bouncing balls and surfaces,

01:44:45.500 --> 01:44:48.900
you can make systems that solve uncomputable problems.

01:44:48.900 --> 01:44:52.580
And so almost any non-trivial physical system

01:44:52.580 --> 01:44:54.740
is computationally universal.

01:44:54.740 --> 01:44:57.700
So the first part of the answer to your question is,

