But the reason I say that is this interesting group

01:47:33.140 --> 01:47:36.620
of strange people who helped invent quantum computing

01:47:36.620 --> 01:47:39.400
before it was clear anything was there.

01:47:40.420 --> 01:47:43.220
One of the main reasons they did it wasn't

01:47:43.260 --> 01:47:46.460
to make a computer that can break a crypto system.

01:47:46.460 --> 01:47:48.900
It was you could turn this backwards.

01:47:48.900 --> 01:47:52.340
You could be surprised quantum mechanics can compute

01:47:52.340 --> 01:47:55.300
or you can go in the opposite direction

01:47:55.300 --> 01:47:58.580
and say if quantum mechanics can compute,

01:48:00.060 --> 01:48:01.900
that's a description of nature.

01:48:01.900 --> 01:48:05.660
So physics is written in terms

01:48:05.660 --> 01:48:08.340
of partial differential equations.

01:48:08.340 --> 01:48:11.860
That is an information technology

01:48:11.860 --> 01:48:15.260
from two centuries ago.

01:48:17.540 --> 01:48:21.260
The equations of physics are not,

01:48:21.260 --> 01:48:22.740
this would sound very strange to say,

01:48:22.740 --> 01:48:24.140
but the equations of physics,

01:48:24.140 --> 01:48:26.180
Schrodinger's equations and Maxwell's equations

01:48:26.180 --> 01:48:28.820
and all of them are not fundamental.

01:48:28.820 --> 01:48:31.020
They're a representation of physics

01:48:31.020 --> 01:48:33.220
that was accessible to us

01:48:33.220 --> 01:48:35.740
in the era of having a pencil and a piece of paper.

01:48:38.380 --> 01:48:41.540
They have a fundamental problem

01:48:41.540 --> 01:48:45.580
which is if you make a dot on a piece of paper

01:48:45.580 --> 01:48:48.540
in traditional physics theory,

01:48:48.540 --> 01:48:51.860
there's infinite information in that dot.

01:48:51.860 --> 01:48:55.360
A point has infinite information.

01:48:56.700 --> 01:49:00.740
That can't be true because information

01:49:00.740 --> 01:49:05.740
is a fundamental resource that's connected to energy.

01:49:05.980 --> 01:49:09.980
And in fact, one of my favorite questions

01:49:09.980 --> 01:49:14.140
you can ask a cosmologist to trip them up is ask,

01:49:14.140 --> 01:49:17.780
is information a conserved quantity in the universe?

01:49:17.780 --> 01:49:20.300
Was all the information created in the Big Bang

01:49:20.300 --> 01:49:21.980
or can the universe create information?

01:49:21.980 --> 01:49:26.620
And I've yet to meet a cosmologist who doesn't stutter

01:49:26.620 --> 01:49:31.620
and not clearly know how to handle that existential question,

01:49:31.900 --> 01:49:35.220
but sort of putting that to a side,

01:49:35.220 --> 01:49:38.060
in physics theory, the way it's taught,

01:49:38.900 --> 01:49:43.260
information comes late.

01:49:43.260 --> 01:49:46.420
You're taught about X, a variable,

01:49:46.420 --> 01:49:48.220
which can contain infinite information,

01:49:48.220 --> 01:49:50.380
but physically that's unrealistic.

01:49:50.380 --> 01:49:53.940
And so physics theories have to find ways to cut that off.

01:49:53.940 --> 01:49:57.860
So instead, there are a number of people

01:49:58.780 --> 01:50:03.220
who start with a theory of the universe

01:50:03.220 --> 01:50:06.660
should start with information and computation

01:50:06.700 --> 01:50:09.580
as the fundamental resources that explain nature.

01:50:09.580 --> 01:50:11.740
And then you build up from that

01:50:11.740 --> 01:50:15.820
to something that looks like throwing baseballs down a slope.

01:50:15.820 --> 01:50:20.820
And so in that sense, the work on physics and computation

01:50:22.140 --> 01:50:24.660
has many applications that we've been talking about,

01:50:24.660 --> 01:50:29.060
but more deeply, it's really getting at new ways

01:50:29.060 --> 01:50:31.220
to think about how the universe works.

01:50:31.220 --> 01:50:32.780
And there are a number of things

01:50:32.780 --> 01:50:34.860
that are hard to do in traditional physics

01:50:34.860 --> 01:50:37.580
that make more sense when you start with information

01:50:37.580 --> 01:50:41.260
and computation as the root of physical theory.

01:50:41.260 --> 01:50:42.620
So information and computation

01:50:42.620 --> 01:50:46.060
being the real fundamental thing in the universe.

01:50:46.060 --> 01:50:49.020
Right, that information is a resource.

01:50:49.020 --> 01:50:52.900
You can have infinite information in finite space.

01:50:53.780 --> 01:50:56.340
Information propagates and interacts,

01:50:56.340 --> 01:50:58.780
and from there you erect the scaffolding of physics.

01:50:58.780 --> 01:51:01.540
Now it happens, the words I just said

01:51:01.540 --> 01:51:04.340
look a lot like quantum field theories.

01:51:05.620 --> 01:51:07.380
But there's an interesting way

01:51:07.380 --> 01:51:11.060
where instead of starting with differential equations

01:51:11.060 --> 01:51:13.020
to get to quantum field theories

01:51:13.020 --> 01:51:16.260
and quantum field theories, you get to quantization.

01:51:18.380 --> 01:51:21.300
If you start from computation and information,

01:51:21.300 --> 01:51:24.740
you begin sort of quantized and you build up from there.

01:51:24.740 --> 01:51:29.300
And so that's the sense in which absolutely,

01:51:29.300 --> 01:51:31.260
I think about the universe as a computer.

01:51:31.300 --> 01:51:34.180
The easy way to understand that is

01:51:36.100 --> 01:51:38.940
just almost anything is computationally universal,

01:51:38.940 --> 01:51:41.980
but the deep way is it's a real fundamental way

01:51:41.980 --> 01:51:43.980
to understand how the universe works.

01:51:45.940 --> 01:51:47.620
Let me go a little bit to the personal

01:51:47.620 --> 01:51:50.500
and the center of bits and atoms.

